TEST_1.content: This is one of the Biggest Sai Baba Temples In India located in Parbhani district of Maharashtra. It is said that Sai Baba was born in the village named Pathri and this temple was constructed in the year 1994 as a memorial.During 1999 this Famous Sai Baba Temples In India was inaugurated for the public. The temple also has a Trust, the primary aim of Trust is to spread knowledge and teach the right things to mankind.Shri V.B Kher was a Sai devotee and he majorly contributed to the establishment of Shri Sai Janmashthan Mandir. He is also a researcher and did detailed research in the year 1975, this is how he discovered the Birthplace of Shri Sai Baba i.e. the Pathri village. It is said that during the digging work of temple building, 2 basements with two arches and tunnel was discovered. It also includes 1 Hanuman idol, workshop articles like pali and panchpatra. The Shri Sai Janmasthan Mandir has daily 5 worship schedule that mean from KakadArati to Shejarati. The temple also conducts 3 prominent festivals every year. The Shri Ram Navami festival is conducted during March and April. The devotees celebrate Guru Poornima in July and during October, Vijayadashami is celebrated as Sai Baba Mahasamadhi.

The Shirdi Sai Baba temple is one of the oldest and Biggest Sai Baba Temples In India. This Sai Baba temple is located in Mylapore and was built in the year 1952 by Mr. Narasimhaswami who hails from Salem.Shirdi Sai Baba Temple is managed by All India Sai Samaj and it was found 7 decades back by Mr. Narasimhaswami. The main objective is to propagate the life, teaching, and principles of Sai Baba. The holy fire is lightened continuously by the devotees and they are allowed to touch Sai Baba’s feet and statue. The big size Sai Baba statue is made using the finest white marble.   When you visit the Shirdi Sai Baba Temple in Mylapore you are free to offer garlands, clothes and even prasad. The temple is pleasant and devotees surely feel positive vibes here.If you want to have a peaceful praying experience, the Shirdi Sai Baba temple is an ideal choice. The religious ambiance will instantly bring inner peace. The biggest attraction of  Shirdi Sai Baba temple is the Jyothi in Shirdi, it is said that this aflame was lit by the deceased saint.  The temple opens at 5:00 am and shuts as 9:00 pm. It remains closed from 1:00 pm to 4:00 pm. The Shirdi Sai Baba temple is an ideal place for exploring spirituality. The temple also offers routine anna dhananam and prasadham. This temple is spacious and has a peaceful aura.
